<br>
Now imagine that these things might not even be green to that named mob you can't quite kill normally.  Perhaps you even get a &quot;host&quot; of the new pets, however powerful they end up being (which I'm hoping is AT LEAST on par with the epic pet, preferably better in at least one aspect).  Which in my opinion would still be balanced considering the host of elements only stays up for 60 seconds and probably has a 72 minute refresh timer.<br>
<br>
Now I realize Verant has lots of room to play with this spell, considering how powerful it can be, but don't flame me over hoping this might actually be useful, and possibly even powerful.  Perhaps they can even add a drawback to it, like you can't summon a normal pet for 6 minutes after the Host of Elements disperses or something to that effect, just so they can make the Host as powerful as possible.  Only time will tell.<br>
<br>
So, any speculation on what these pets will be?  Perhaps they will all be generic melee-only pets and zerg the mob to death.  Or maybe they will be a few of each of the pets, having an earth pets sit there and tank, while the water pets get behind the mob and backstab, with air stunning and fire nuking, creating a little group (sounds like lots of work from a programmer's standpoint - I wouldn't want to code that anyway - probably only wishful thinking).  Any other ideas? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucyricusbloodbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyricus Bloodbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1000<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 8:17:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://520013139003-001.bei.t-online.de/IWD_Human_Male_Wizard3.gif height=58 width=36></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Could it be???</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
